				\begin{document}$$ {B}_i=\left(1-\frac{C_t}{C_i}\right)\times 100 $$\end{document}Bi=1−CtCi×100where Bi is the natural decay rate, Ci is the measured value 1 h after injecting bacteria, and Ct is the measured value 2 h after injecting bacteria.

The initial value’s corrected value is calculated using Eq. (2)2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
