				\begin{document}$$ {S}_c=\left(1-\frac{B_i}{100}\right)\times {P}_t $$\end{document}Sc=1−Bi100×Ptwhere Sc is the initial value’s corrected value (CFU/m3), Bi is the natural decay rate, and Pt is the initial value (CFU/m3).

The airborne bacteria removal rate was defined as3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
